Java is a popular high-level,object-oriented programming language that was originally developed by Sun Microsystems and released in 1995. 
Currently, Java is owned by Oracle and more than 3 billion devices run Java.
Java runs on a variety of platforms, such as Windows, Mac OS, and the various versions of UNIX.
Today Java is being used to develop numerous types of software applications, 
including desktop apps, mobile apps, web apps, games, and much more.
 
